The paper deals with a communication channel model and its application to cellular communications. Specifically, it considers the input-erasure Gaussian channel and studies its properties in the context of a linear cellular uplink. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Communications (cs.COMM), and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses mathematical tools such as tri-diagonal matrices and infinite sums, which are commonly used in Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY), respectively. Therefore, these two sub-categories are also likely candidates.
